    <article class="privacy-page">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <strong class="date">Last updated: May 2019</strong>
      <p>Your privacy is important to us. This privacy policy explains what personal data Horizon Hobby collects from you, through our interactions with you, and how we use that data.</p>
      <p>Horizon Hobby offers a wide range of websites to assist customers across the globe. Please read the site-specific details in this privacy statement, which provide additional details about some of Horizon Hobby's websites.</p>
      <p>You can freely access much of our websites without providing any personal information. But certain functions of our website, for example purchasing products, entering contests, filling out surveys, and receiving newsletters, emails, or other promotional information from us, require that you submit some personal information. We do not collect any personal information without providing adequate notice and choice.</p>
      <div id="accordion" class="accordion">
         <div class="card">
            <section>
               <div class="card-header" id="topic-1">
                  <button aria-controls="collapseTopic-1" aria-expanded="false" class="btn btn-link" data-parent="#accordion" data-target="#collapseTopic-1" data-toggle="collapse">Your Rights Concerning Personally Identifiable Information</button>
                  <div aria-labelledby="topic-1" class="collapse m-1 p-1" data-parent="#accordion" id="collapseTopic-1">
                     <p>You always have the right to request information about your stored data, its origin, its recipients, and the purpose of its collection at no charge. You also have the right to request that it be corrected, blocked, or deleted. You can <a href="https://www.horizonhobby.de/en_DE/contact" title="Go to Contact Us">Contact Us </a> if you have further questions about privacy and data protection.</p>
                     <a class="multi-btn-link" aria-controls="#reveal-1" aria-expanded="false" data-target="#reveal-1" data-toggle="collapse" href="javascript:void(0);">Learn More</a>
                     <div class="multi-collapse m-1" id="reveal-1">
                        <p>Many data processing operations are only possible with your express consent. You may revoke consent for these data processing operations at any time to stop future processing. An informal email making this request is sufficient. The data processed before we receive your request may still be legally processed depending on the nature of the data and Horizon Hobby's legal requirements or legitimate interest in such data.</p>
                        <p>You have the right to have data that we process based on your consent or in fulfillment of a contract delivered to yourself or to a third party in a standard, machine-readable format. If you require the direct transfer of data to another responsible party, this will only be done to the extent technically feasible. Horizon Hobby may require reasonable actions of the requester, such as the use of confirmation codes, prior to delivery, to protect users' personal information from potential malicious third parties.</p>
                        <p>If there has been a breach of data protection legislation, the person affected may file a complaint with the competent regulatory authorities. The competent regulatory authority for matters related to data protection in the European Union is the data protection officer of the German state in which our subsidiary, Horizon Hobby GmbH, is headquartered, Schleswig-Holstein. The contact information for the data protection officer for Schleswig-Holstein can be found at the following link: <a href="https://www.bfdi.bund.de/SharedDocs/Adressen/LfD/SchleswigHolstein.html" target="_blank">https://www.bfdi.bund.de/SharedDocs/Adressen/LfD/SchleswigHolstein.html</a>. The competent regulatory authority for matters related to data protection in the United States is the Federal Trade Commission, which receives complaints at <a href="https://www.ftccomplaintassistant.gov/" target="blank">www.ftccomplaintassistant.gov/</a>.</p>
                     </div>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </section>
         </div>
         <div class="card">
            <section>
               <div class="card-header" id="topic-2">
                  <button aria-controls="collapseTopic-2" aria-expanded="false" class="btn btn-link" data-target="#collapseTopic-2" data-toggle="collapse">Notice Concerning the Data Protection Officers and Party Responsible for Horizon Hobby Websites</button>
                  <div aria-labelledby="topic-2" class="collapse m-1 p-1" data-parent="#accordion" id="collapseTopic-2">
                     <p>The party responsible for processing data on our US-based websites intended for American and other non-European users, such as horizonhobby.com, towerhobbies.com, spectrum.com, axialracing.com, etc., is:</p>
                     <address><i>Horizon Hobby LLC<br />
                        2904 Research Road.<br />
                        Champaign, IL 61822<br />
                        Phone: 1(217)352-1913</i><br />
                        <a href="https://www.horizonhobby.de/en_DE/contact" title="Go to Contact Us">Contact Us </a>
                     </address>
                     <p>Our Data Protection Officer for these US-based sites is Ben Ambrose, who can be reached through the above channels or directly at <a mailto="dpo@horizonhobby.com">dpo@horizonhobby.com</a>.</p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </section>
         </div>
         <div class="card">
            <section>
               <div class="card-header" id="topic-3">
                  <button aria-controls="collapseTopic-3" aria-expanded="false" class="btn btn-link" data-target="#collapseTopic-3" data-toggle="collapse">Types of Data We Collect</button>
                  <div aria-labelledby="topic-3" class="collapse m-1 p-1" data-parent="#accordion" id="collapseTopic-3">
                     <p>Our goal is to provide you with the best and most efficient service as possible so you can get back to your hobbies. Horizon Hobby collects data to help us provide this service. We use the data that we collect about you to fulfill your product and service purchases and to create a personalized online experience. In order to better provide you with these products and services, our websites collect two types of information about users: Personally Identifiable and Non-Personally Identifiable Information.</p>
                     <a class="multi-btn-link" aria-controls="#reveal-2" aria-expanded="false" data-target="#reveal-2" data-toggle="collapse" href="javascript:void(0);">Learn More</a>
                     <div class="multi-collapse m-1 p-1" id="reveal-2">
                        <h3>Non-Personal Data We Collect</h3>
                        <p>We gather certain information about you based upon where you shop on our site in several ways. This information is compiled and analyzed on both an individual and aggregated basis. For example, this information may include the Uniform Resource Locator (&quot;URL&quot;) of the website you came from, the URL you go to next, the browser you are using, and your Internet Protocol (&quot;IP&quot;) address. A URL is the global address of documents and other resources on the World Wide Web. An IP address is an identifier for a computer or device on a Transmission Control Protocol/Internet Protocol (&quot;TCP/IP&quot;) network, such as the World Wide Web. Networks like the Web use TCP/IP to route information based on the IP address of the destination. In other words, an IP address is a number that is automatically assigned to your computer whenever you are surfing the web and allows web servers to locate and identify your computer. Computers require IP addresses for users to communicate on the Internet, browse, and shop.</p>
                        <h3>Personal Data We Collect</h3>
                        <p>Personal information is requested when you order a product, register for a Wish List, enter contests or sweepstakes, fill out surveys, send us feedback, and send us mailings. For example, this information might include but is not limited to your name, billing address, shipping address, telephone number, email address, credit card or other payment information, and product details. With this information, our online catalog can fill your orders and better provide you with personalized services.</p>
                        <p>Most personal information collected by Horizon Hobby is necessary for the completion of purchase orders. Other personal data is collected with your consent. Horizon Hobby works to provide users with as much relevant information as possible prior to collecting any personal data.</p>
                     </div>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </section>
         </div>
         <div class="card">
            <section>
               <div class="card-header" id="topic-4">
                  <button aria-controls="collapseTopic-4" aria-expanded="false" class="btn btn-link" data-target="#collapseTopic-4" data-toggle="collapse">How We Collect Data</button>
                  <div aria-labelledby="topic-4" class="collapse m-1 p-1" data-parent="#accordion" id="collapseTopic-4">
                     <h3>Cookies</h3>
                     <p>Some of our web pages include cookies. You can configure your browser to selectively or always reject cookies. But disabling or rejecting cookies may limit the functionality of this website. Cookies, which are necessary to allow electronic communications or to provide certain functions you use, are stored pursuant to GDPR Art. 6(1)(f), which allows the processing for a legitimate interest. Horizon Hobby has a legitimate interest in the storage of cookies to ensure an optimized service provided free of technical errors. Cookies stored for other purposes, such as customizing your online experience, are treated separately in this privacy policy.</p>
                     <a class="multi-btn-link" aria-controls="#reveal-3" aria-expanded="false" data-target="#reveal-3" data-toggle="collapse" href="javascript:void(0);">Learn More</a><br />
                     &nbsp;
                     <div class="multi-collapse m-1" id="reveal-3">
                        <p>Cookies are small text files that are stored on your computer and saved by your browser. Cookies do not harm your computer and do not contain any viruses. Most of the cookies we use are session cookies that are automatically deleted after your visit. Other cookies make it possible to recognize your browser when you next visit the site.</p>
                        <p>You can configure your browser or browser plug-ins to inform you about the use of cookies so that you can decide on a case-by-case basis whether to accept or reject a cookie. Also, your browser can be configured to automatically accept cookies under certain conditions, to always reject them, or to automatically delete cookies when closing your browser.</p>
                     </div>
                     <h3>Web Beacons</h3>
                     <p>Some Horizon Hobby web pages include web beacons. Web beacons are small, graphic images on web pages or web-based documents or in email messages. We use web beacons to personalize your experience on some Horizon Hobby websites, determine the usefulness of information our services provide, and to analyze general user traffic patterns. Information about specific uses of web beacons on Horizon Hobby web pages can be found under the Analytics and Advertising section of this privacy policy.</p>
                     <h3>Server Log Files</h3>
                     <p>The website provider automatically collects and stores information that your browser automatically transmits to us in server log files. These include the type and version of your browser, operating system used, referrer URL, the hostname of the accessing computer, time of the server request, and IP address. These data are not combined with data from other sources. The basis for data processing is GDPR Art. 6(1)(b), which allows the processing of data to fulfill a contract or for measures preliminary to a contract.</p>
                     <h3>Contact Forms</h3>
                     <p>Should you send us questions via the <a href="https://www.horizonhobby.de/en_DE/contact" title="Go to Contact Us">Contact Us form</a>, we will collect the data entered on the form, including the contact details you provide to answer your question and any follow-up questions. We do not share this information without your permission. Therefore, we will process data you enter onto the contact form only with your consent under GDPR Art. 6(1)(a). You may revoke your consent at any time by making a request via the contact form. We will retain the data you provide on the contact form until you request its deletion, revoke your consent for its storage, or the purpose of its storage ceases to exist. Mandatory provisions, especially mandatory data retention periods, remain unaffected by this provision.</p>
                     <h3>Registration on Horizon Hobby Websites</h3>
                     <p>Some Horizon Hobby websites allow you to register with the website to access additional functions offered here. The input data will only be used for the purpose of using the respective site or service for which you registered. We will process the data provided during registration based on your consent under GDPR Art. 6(1)(a). You may revoke your consent at any time by sending a request via the <a href="https://www.horizonhobby.de/en_DE/contact" title="Go to Contact Us">Contact Us form</a>. We will continue to store the data collected during registration for as long as you remain registered on our website. Mandatory provisions, especially mandatory data retention periods, remain unaffected by this provision.</p>
                     <a class="multi-btn-link" aria-controls="#reveal-4" aria-expanded="false" data-target="#reveal-4" data-toggle="collapse" href="javascript:void(0);">Learn More</a><br />
                     &nbsp;
                     <div class="multi-collapse m-1" id="reveal-4">
                        <p>The mandatory information requested during registration must be provided in full. Otherwise, we will reject your registration. If the registration form is rejected, we do not collect the information in the registration form fields. To inform you about important changes, such as those within the scope of our site or technical changes, we will use the email address specified during registration. You may unsubscribe from these emails using the link provided in the email.</p>
                     </div>
                     <h3>Leaving Comments on Horizon Hobby Websites</h3>
                     <p>Some Horizon Hobby websites allow you to leave comments or reviews. If you use the comment or review function on the sites, the time at which you created the comment and your email address will be stored along with your comment, as well as your username, unless you are posting anonymously. Our comment or review function may store the IP address of those users who posted. We need this information to be able to pursue actions for illegal or slanderous content. The comments and reviews are stored based on your consent under GDPR Art. 6(1)(a). You may revoke your consent at any time by contacting us via the&nbsp;<a href="/en_GB/contact">contact form</a>. Mandatory provisions, especially mandatory data retention periods or obligations to maintain records.</p>
                     <a class="multi-btn-link" aria-controls="#reveal-5" aria-expanded="false" data-target="#reveal-5" data-toggle="collapse" href="javascript:void(0);">Learn More</a><br />
                     &nbsp;
                     <div class="multi-collapse m-1" id="reveal-5">
                        <p>On some Horizon Hobby websites, you may be able to sign up to receive the comment feed after registering or commenting. Your email address may be checked with a confirmation email. You can unsubscribe from this function at any time by clicking the unsubscribe link in the emails. The data provided by subscribing to the comments feed will be deleted. But if you have submitted comments or provided the data to us for another purpose or elsewhere, those comments or data will not be deleted. You may request the deletion of this data by sending an informal request via our <a href="https://www.horizonhobby.de/en_DE/contact" title="Go to Contact Us">Contact Us</a> form</p>
                     </div>
                     <h3>Plugins</h3>
                     <p>Some Horizon Hobby websites have social media or other types of plugins to improve our customer's online experience. Social media plugins allow users to engage with their social media pages. Horizon Hobby pages may include plugins to Facebook, Twitter, Google+, Instagram, Tumblr, LinkedIn, Pinterest, Snapchat, YouTube, Vimeo, or Google Maps. When you visit our site, a direct connection between your browser and the social media company's server is established. This allows the social media company to process the users' engagement with their social media plug-in. To establish this connection, the social media company receives information that you have visited our site from your IP address. Horizon Hobby has a legitimate interest in creating an engaging user experience on its webpages. Thus, the basis for data processing under the GDPR is Art. 6(1)(f). Information about each social media plugin can be found in the Learn More section of this provision.</p>
                     <a class="multi-btn-link" aria-controls="#reveal-6" aria-expanded="false" data-target="#reveal-6" data-toggle="collapse" href="javascript:void(0);">Learn More</a><br />
                     &nbsp;
                     <div class="multi-collapse m-1" id="reveal-6">
                        <h4>Facebook plugins</h4>
                        <p>Facebook plugins allow users to connect to their Facebook accounts. They are operated by Facebook Inc., 1 Hacker Way, Menlo Park, California, 94025, USA. The Facebook plugins can be recognized by the Facebook logo or Like button on our sites. For an overview of the Facebook plugins, see <a href="https://developers.facebook.com/docs/plugins/" target="_blank">developers.facebook.com/docs/plugins/.</a></p>
                        <p>When you visit our site, a direct connection between your browser and the Facebook server is established via the plugin. This enables Facebook to receive information that you have visited our site from your IP address. If you click on the Facebook &quot;Like&quot; or share button while you are logged into your Facebook account, you can link the content of our site to your Facebook profile. This allows Facebook to associate visits to our site with your user account. Please note that, as the operator of this site, we have no knowledge of the content of the data transmitted to Facebook or of how Facebook uses these data.</p>
                        <p>For more information, please see Facebook's privacy policy at <a href="https://facebook.com/policy.php" target="_blank">facebook.com/policy.php. </a>If you do not want Facebook to associate your visit to our site with your Facebook account, please log out of your Facebook account.</p>
                        <h4>Twitter Plugin</h4>
                        <p>The Twitter plugin allows users to connect to their Twitter account. It is operated by Twitter Inc., 1355 Market Street, Suite 900, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA. The Twitter plugin can be recognized by the Twitter bird logo. For an overview of the Twitter plugin, see <a href="https://dev.twitter.com/web/overview" target="_blank">dev.twitter.com/web/overview.</a></p>
                        <h4>Google+ plugin</h4>
                        <p>The Google+ plugin allows users to connect to their Google+ account. It is operated by Google Inc., 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043, USA. The Google+ plugin can be recognized by the &quot;G+&quot; Google logo. For an overview of the Google+ plugin, see <a href="https://developers.google.com/+/web/" target="_blank">developers.google.com/+/web/.</a></p>
                        <p>Collection and disclosure of information: Using the Google +1 button allows you to publish information worldwide. By means of the Google+ button, you and other users can receive custom content from Google and our partners. Google stores both the fact that you have +1'd a piece of content and information about the page you were viewing when you clicked +1. Your +1 can be displayed together with your profile name and photo in Google services, for example in search results or in your Google profile, or in other places on websites and advertisements on the Internet. Google records information about your +1 activities to improve Google services for you and others.</p>
                        <p>To use the Google + button, you need a globally visible, public Google profile that must contain at least the name chosen for the profile. This name is used by all Google services. In some cases, this name may also replace a different name that you have used to share content via your Google account. The identity of your Google profile can be shown to users who know your email address or other information that can identify you.</p>
                        <p>Use of collected data: In addition to the uses mentioned above, the information you provide is used in accordance with the applicable Google data protection policies. Google may publish summary statistics about users' +1 activity or share it with users and partners, such as publishers, advertisers, or affiliate websites. For more information, please see Google's privacy policy at <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">policies.google.com/privacy.</a></p>
                        <h4>Instagram plugin</h4>
                        <p>The Instagram plugin allows users to connect to their Instagram account. It is operated by Instagram Inc., 1601 Willow Road, Menlo Park, CA 94025, USA. The Instagram plugin can be recognized by the Instagram camera logo. For an overview of the Instagram plugin, see <a href="https://www.instagram.com/developer/">www.instagram.com/developer/</a>.</p>
                        <p>When you visit our site, a direct connection between your browser and the Instagram server is established via the plugin. This enables Instagram to receive information that you have visited our site from your IP address. If you click on the &quot;Instagram camera button&quot; while you are logged into your Instagram account, you can link the content of our site to your Instagram profile. This allows Instagram to associate visits to our site with your user account. Please note that, as the operator of this site, we have no knowledge of the content of the data transmitted to Instagram or of how Instagram uses these data.</p>
                        <h4>Tumblr plugin</h4>
                        <p>The Tumblr plugin allows users to connect to their Tumblr account. It is operated by Tumblr, Inc., 35 East 21st St., 10th Floor, New York, NY 10010, USA. The Tumblr plugin can be recognized by the Tumblr logo.</p>
                        <p>When you visit our site, a direct connection between your browser and the Instagram server is established via the plugin. This enables Instagram to receive information that you have visited our site from your IP address. If you click on the &quot;Tumblr&quot; button while you are logged into your Tumblr account, you can link the content of our site to your Tumblr profile. This allows Tumblr to associate visits to our site with your user account. Please note that, as the operator of this site, we have no knowledge of the content of the data transmitted to Instagram or of how Tumblr uses these data.</p>
                        <p>For more information, please see Tumblr's privacy policy at <a href="https://www.tumblr.com/policy/en/privacy" target="_blank">www.tumblr.com/policy/en/privacy</a>. If you do not want Tumblr to associate your visit to our site with your Instagram account, please log out of your Instagram account.</p>
                        <h4>LinkedIn plugin</h4>
                        <p>The LinkedIn plugin allows users to connect to their LinkedIn account. It is operated by LinkedIn, a subsidiary of Microsoft, at LinkedIn Corporation, 2029 Stierlin Court, Mountain View, CA 94043, USA. The LinkedIn plugin can be recognized by the LinkedIn logo on our sites. For an overview of the LinkedIn plugin, see&nbsp;<a href="https://developer.linkedin.com/plugins">developer.linkedin.com/plugins</a>.</p>
                        <p>When you visit our site, a direct connection between your browser and the LinkedIn server is established via the plugin. This enables LinkedIn to receive information that you have visited our site from your IP address. If you click on the LinkedIn &quot;Recommend&quot; button while you are logged into your LinkedIn account, you can link the content of our site to your Facebook profile. This allows LinkedIn to associate visits to our site with your user account. Please note that, as the operator of this site, we have no knowledge of the content of the data transmitted to LinkedIn or of how LinkedIn uses these data.</p>
                        <p>For more information, please see LinkedIn's privacy policy at<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank">www.linkedin.com/legal/privacy-policy</a>. If you do not want LinkedIn to associate your visit to our site with your LinkedIn account, please log out of your LinkedIn account.</p>
                        <h4>Pinterest plugin</h4>
                        <p>The Pinterest plugin allows users to connect to their Pinterest account. It is operated by Pinterest Inc., 635 High Street, Palo Alto, CA, 94301, USA. The Pinterest plugin can be recognized by the Pinterest &quot;Pin it&quot; logo. For an overview of the Pinterest plugins, see&nbsp;<a href="https://about.pinterest.com/en/browser-button" target="_blank">about.pinterest.com/en/browser-button</a>.</p>
                        <p>When you visit our site, a direct connection between your browser and the Pinterest server is established via the plugin. This enables Pinterest to receive information that you have visited our site from your IP address. If you click on the Pinterest &quot;Pin it&quot; button while you are logged into your Pinterest account, you can link the content of our site to your Pinterest profile. This allows Pinterest to associate visits to our site with your user account. Please note that, as the operator of this site, we have no knowledge of the content of the data transmitted to Pinterest or of how Pinterest uses these data.</p>
                        <p>For more information, please see Pinterest's privacy policy at <a href="https://www.policy.pinterest.com/en/privacy-policy" target="_blank">policy.pinterest.com/en/privacy-policy</a>.If you do not want Pinterest to associate your visit to our site with your Pinterest account, please log out of your Pinterest account.</p>
                        <h4>Snapchat plugin</h4>
                        <p>The Snapchat plugin allows users to connect to their Snapchat account. It is operated by Snap Inc., 63 Market Street, Venice, CA 90291, USA. The Snapchat plugin can be recognized by the Snapchat &quot;Ghost&quot; logo. For an overview of the Snapchat plugins, see <a href="http://developers.snapchat.com/">developers.snapchat.com/</a>.</p>
                        <p>When you visit our site, a direct connection between your browser and the Snapchat server is established via the plugin. This enables Snapchat to receive information that you have visited our site from your IP address. If you click on the Snapchat &quot;Ghost&quot; button while you are logged into your Snapchat account, you can link the content of our site to your Snapchat profile. This allows Snapchat to associate visits to our site with your user account. Please note that, as the operator of this site, we have no knowledge of the content of the data transmitted to Snapchat or of how Snapchat uses these data.</p>
                        <p>For more information, please see Snapchat's privacy policy at <a href="http://www.snap.com/privacy/privacy-policy/">www.snap.com/privacy/privacy-policy/</a>. If you do not want Snapchat to associate your visit to our site with your Snapchat account, please log out of your Snapchat account.</p>
